{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"agent_message","text":"Implementation plan:\n1. Add a shared worker-monitor event stream in `ccode-tools` and publish events from `agent` (Running/Completed/Failed) and `task_stop` (Cancelled) so coordinator updates can reach TUI as they happen.\n2. Extend TUI state with a dedicated worker panel model: task list, selection, compact details (`task_id`, `summary`, `started_at`, `updated_at`), plus virtualized list rendering for high-volume task history.\n3. Add keyboard controls for panel navigation and stop action on selected running task, then execute stop via existing `task_stop` tool path from TUI runtime.\n4. Update draw layout to render the worker panel beside conversation, and wire real-time monitor events into the panel.\n5. Add/adjust unit tests first for panel state behavior, then implement code to make them pass.\n6. Run `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings`, and `cargo test --workspace`, then commit with your exact message."}}
